OL,3,CMan jailed for scamming in-laws by
OL,4,Cforging contract with Paris Saint-
OL,5,CGermain
OL,7,FAt the same time, he also took out a
OL,8,Fshort-term bridging loan of #1.68m
OL,9,Ffrom a finance company using the fake
OL,10,Fcontract again as assurance of income,
OL,11,Fand even forged his wife's signature
OL,12,Fto purchase the house.
OL,14,FBlackmore went on to repeatedly fail
OL,15,Fto pay back the loan to his in-laws,
OL,16,Fclaiming the money from the club had
OL,17,Fbeen paid into the wrong account, that
OL,18,Fthe bank had frozen the payment and
OL,19,Fother lies.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/13
