OL,7,FIn a Victim Personal Statement, his
OL,8,Fmother-in-law said: "Mr Blackmore's
OL,9,Fdeception has had a profound effect on
OL,10,Four entire family ` physically,
OL,11,Femotionally, psychologically and
OL,12,Ffinancially.
OL,14,F"We continue to struggle to comprehend
OL,15,Fthe utter betrayal, having embraced Mr
OL,16,FBlackmore into our family.
OL,18,F"Emotionally, my trust has been broken
OL,19,Fand I feel totally betrayed by this
OL,20,Fgrandiose narcissist.
